Before Trigger  -  update,delete,insert (before the things are committed or stored in the database) - To do the operations on the same object
After Trigger  -   to a related record - update,delete,insert,undelete(restoring the record)
trigger AccountTrigger on Account(before insert)
{
 for(Account acc : Trigger.new)
 {
   if(acc.Rating == 'null')
    {
      acc.Rating = 'Warm';
    }
 }
}
Context Variables -> describes exact what the description 
Trigger.new - contains the list of newly created records


